Stay Safe Online: Prevention Checklist

🛡️ General Cyber Safety Tips

Enable Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA): Always add an extra layer of security to your university and social media accounts.
Verify the Sender: Before clicking any links in an "urgent" email, check the sender's full email address for subtle misspellings.
Use Strong, Unique Passwords: Avoid using the same password across different platforms; use a mix of symbols, numbers, and letters.
Think Before You Click: Hover your mouse over any link to see the actual destination URL before clicking it.
Keep Software Updated: Regularly update your browser and operating system to protect against known security vulnerabilities.
Be Wary of Public Wi-Fi: Avoid logging into sensitive accounts or making financial transactions while connected to unsecured public networks.
💸 UPI & Financial Safety (Mandatory)

No PIN for Receiving Money: Never enter your UPI PIN to receive money; a PIN is only required to send or pay money.
QR Code Caution: Do not scan QR codes sent by unknown individuals, as these are frequently used in "request money" scams.
🚨 How to Report Cybercrime in India

If you fall victim to a digital scam or notice suspicious activity, report it immediately through official channels:

National Cyber Crime Portal: cybercrime.gov.in
National Helpline: Call 1930 (Available 24/7)
